#### ExceptionErrorEnum

**Note:** `ExceptionErrorEnum` is different for every repository but always includes the general exceptions:

```java
public enum ExceptionErrorEnum {
    // General exceptions (always present)
    BAD_REQUEST("SYST-0001"),
    HANDLE_SERVER_EXCEPTION("SYST-0002"),
    ACCESS_DENIED("SYST-0003"),
    UNAUTHORIZED("SYST-0004"),
    BUSINESS_ERROR("SYST-0005"),
    
    // Attribute and forms exceptions (always present)
    REQUIRED_ATTRIBUTE("ATTR-0001"),
    INVALID_VALUE("ATTR-0002"),
    
    // Repository-specific exceptions (vary by repository)
    // Example for user service:
    USER_NOT_FOUND("USER-0001"),
    USER_ALREADY_EXISTS("USER-0007"),
    
    // Example for project service:
    PROJECT_NOT_FOUND("PROJ-0001"),
    PROJECT_DELETED("PROJ-0002"),
    
    // Example for resource service:
    RESOURCE_NOT_FOUND("RES-0001"),
    RESOURCE_NOT_ASSOCIATED("RES-0002"),
    USER_NOT_IN_PROJECT("USER-0003"),
    
    // ... add your repository-specific codes here
}
```

