## Usage Examples

### Basic Usage
```java
// Simple error
throw new ServiceException("User not found");

// With resource and HTTP status
throw new ServiceException("User not found", "users", HttpStatus.NOT_FOUND, ExceptionErrorEnum.USER_NOT_FOUND);

// Note: The second parameter ("users") refers to the resource name
```

### Advanced Usage
```java
// With validation errors
List<ObjectError> validationErrors = validator.validate(userDTO);
throw new ServiceException(Level.ERROR, "Validation failed", 
                          ExceptionErrorEnum.INVALID_VALUE, 
                          "users", validationErrors, null, 
                          HttpStatus.BAD_REQUEST, null);

// With additional data
Map<String, Object> data = new HashMap<>();
data.put("userId", userId);
data.put("attemptedAction", "delete");
throw new ServiceException(Level.ERROR, HttpStatus.FORBIDDEN, 
                          ExceptionErrorEnum.USER_NO_PERMISSIONS, data);
```

### Real-World Examples from Codebase
```java
// Catalog client deleted check
if (StatusEnum.getByValue(catalogClient.getStatus()) == StatusEnum.DELETED) {
    throw new ServiceException("Cliente catálogo eliminado", "catalogClients", 
                              HttpStatus.CONFLICT, ExceptionErrorEnum.CATALOG_CLIENT_DELETED);
}

// Resource not associated with project
if (!project.getResources().contains(resource)) {
    throw new ServiceException("Resource not associated with project", "resource", 
                              HttpStatus.CONFLICT, ExceptionErrorEnum.RESOURCE_NOT_ASSOCIATED);
}

// User not in project
throw new ServiceException(Level.ERROR, "User not associated with project", 
                          HttpStatus.CONFLICT, ExceptionErrorEnum.USER_NOT_IN_PROJECT);
```

